g.text: Volition: The damage is truly extraordinary. It's a miracle you don't shit yourself.
Logic: And you *did* unplug the black wire from said breaker box.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Does it say anything interesting?" The lieutenant leans closer to read the crumpled note over your shoulder.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Really?" The lieutenant looks at you, the corner of his mouth curved into a smug grin. "You don't have a single guess?"
A Note from the Fridge: Didn't you see one right next to the breaker box?
You: But why did they leave a filament lying in a freezer?
Logic: It does, but who might that be?

Kim Kitsuragi: "Oh, I'm sure that child would *love* to get his hands on a filament memory -- even if he doesn't know what to do with it. He'd probably try to pawn it for speed, based on our encounter."

A Note from the Fridge: Someone has scribbled: "S, I can't believe the off-site copy is still here! The illiterate ginger kid keeps stealing stuff from the studio, so I had to hide it somewhere safe."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Some local miscreant probably. There are tons of them running around in Martinaise, ready to stir up trouble. We usually dispatch our junior officers to deal with them."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like someone from that radiogame company upstairs. I'm a little surprised they just left their property lying here."
Interfacing: It would be *oh so* fun to try that radiocomputer out for yourself.

A Note from the Fridge: "You'll find the filament memory with the off-site copy in the frozen ice cream maker. Please take it home ASAP, it's important. I'd do it myself if I lived in a civilized place with a freezer. Take care, Sulisław."
Volition: Are you serious? You sure you don't want to hazard a guess here, detective?
Encyclopedia: It's part of a radiocomputer. When not in use, filaments are stored at temperatures below zero.
A Note from the Fridge: The note is written with a blue pencil on a piece of lined office paper. The kitchen magnets have left spots on its surface.
A Note from the Fridge: According to the note, someone named 'Sulisław'.
Interfacing: Perhaps someone who belonged to the defunct radiocomputer company?
"Remind me again -- what's a filament memory?"
Volition: Really? You sure it isn't a certain redhaired little gremlin who refers to himself in the third person?
Volition: Ding, ding, ding! We have a winner!
Logic: Someone who owns a radiocomputer, one might assume.
You: "Maybe it's because of the Entity."
Interfacing: It's like the *production schedule* you found, only this one's an *off-site copy*.
You: "Maybe they had to leave in a hurry."
Esprit de Corps: This is tangential at best, but the lieutenant's *detective instinct* is still active.
"Someone has moved the filament! But who?"
Rhetoric: Which is to say -- not very good.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Sulisław... wasn't he one of Miss Luukanen-Kilde's coworkers?" He tilts his head. "I remember coming across this name when we were reading her personal log."

A Note from the Fridge: Someone has scribbled: "S, I can't believe the off-site copy is still here! The illiterate ginger kid keeps stealing stuff from the studio, so I had to hide it somewhere safe."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Someone who owns a radiocomputer? My guess is as good as yours, officer."
You: Nope. Drawing a blank here.
You: Where's the frozen ice cream maker?
"Do you have any idea where the frozen ice cream maker could be?"
A Note from the Fridge: Somewhere among the shadows in the cellar.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It belongs inside a radiocomputer, storing its memory. It's like a tape -- you listen to disco tapes, right? It's like one of your disco tapes, only for a computer."
A Note from the Fridge: The note doesn't specify.
A Note from the Fridge: The note does not specify.
Reaction Speed: Wasn't he one of Soona's former coworkers?
You: Who's the illiterate ginger kid?

A Note from the Fridge: "You'll find the filament memory with the off-site copy in the frozen ice cream maker. Please take it home ASAP, it's important. I'd do it myself if I lived in a civilized place with a freezer. Take care, Sulisław."
You: Are you talking about Cuno?
A Note from the Fridge: Didn't you see a *melting* ice cream maker right next to the breaker box?
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know... I assume it's somewhere close to the ice bear fridge."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm placing my bets on a certain red-haired miscreant we met before. He'd probably try to pawn it for speed, based on our encounter."
Interfacing: Sounds like a question for a detective, detective.
